As design automation and computer design professionals, we have come to equate VLSI with a chip having 10<supscrpt>6</supscrpt> devices, or 10<supscrpt>5</supscrpt> random logic devices, or 10<supscrpt>5</supscrpt> gates, etc. However, the size argument does not explain what use the system designer will be able to make of such complex devices.